│ The `computeBestVF` function is responsible for determining the best          │
│ vectorization factor (VF) for a loop. The assertion failure occurs because    │
│ the `BestFactor.Width` (determined by the VPlan-based cost model) does not    │
│ match the `LegacyVF.Width` (determined by the legacy cost model), and the     │
│ function `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` does not resolve the         │
│ disagreement.                                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ ### Observations                                                              │
│                                                                               │
│ 1. The assertion at lines 7389–7392 ensures that the VPlan-based and legacy   │
│ cost models agree on the vectorization factor unless the VPlan contains       │
│ additional simplifications.                                                   │
│ 2. The `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` function is used to check if   │
│ the VPlan introduces simplifications that justify the discrepancy.            │
│ 3. The `precomputeCosts` function is used to calculate the cost of the VPlan, │
│ which is then compared with the legacy cost model.                            │
│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause                                                                │
│                                                                               │
│ The discrepancy arises because the VPlan-based cost model and the legacy cost │
│ model use different assumptions or calculations for certain instructions,     │
│ leading to mismatched vectorization factors.                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ ### Proposed Fix                                                              │
│                                                                               │
│ 1. Enhance the `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` function to ensure it  │
│ accurately identifies cases where the VPlan introduces valid simplifications. │
│ 2. Ensure that the `precomputeCosts` function accounts for all relevant       │
│ instructions and scenarios to minimize discrepancies.                         │
│                                                                               │
│ I will now proceed to implement the proposed fix.                             │
